About bbno$

12 contributors

Alexander Gumuchian (b. June 30, 1995), better known by his stage name bbno$ (pronounced baby no money), is a rapper from Vancouver, British Columbia. Posting his first song nah in April of 2016, he ascended the ranks of SoundCloud rapidly, before moving to major streaming platforms.

yeet
July 23, 2019
bbno$ answered a question on a song:
Lalala by Y2K & bbno$

  • How did the song come about?

    bbno$ :

    bbno$: I remember, the day we made this song, I sat down and Ari has a little couch, and that couch is messed up from another rapper. I was moving to the left and all I said to Ari, I was like, Cardi B, I like it like that. And you know, he started playing at riff. I started going, nah, nah, nah, nah, nah. And we both turned at each other and kind of just made a hit I guess.

    Ari: Its funny cause he had never sang a song before that day. This was literally the first time that he had ever tried singing on a song. And so, I think he was sing rapping anothers on kind of. I was like, Oh yeah, you have good tone. Which you cant recreate. You can fix pitch and all that, but you cant fix tone. And so it was kind of an interesting situation. Just first time you ever singing on a track just turned out insane.

    bbno$: It was really funny too. Cause usually when I come up with melodies, when Im making music, I always genuinely forget it and Im like, Fuck. My god. Like come on. So I ended up getting in the booth and literally the take pretty much right before we made the, the full hook was, Yo. Did I really forget that melody? And then I heard him in the back, he was like, Nah, nah, nah, nah, nah, nah. And then it just went into the hook and, it just worked. Its funny cause I just that, that sentence kind of went viral. I just played this song in Edmonton, Canada.
